Package: CATaN
Type: Package
Title: Canonical correlation Analysis of Transcriptome and TF-gene regulatory Networks (CATaN)
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Haruka", "Takahashi", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "harukatakahashi30@keio.jp",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2025-4302")))
Description: CATaN performs Canonical Correlation Analysis (CCA) between
    a transcription factor (TF)-gene regulatory network matrix and transcriptome data
    to identify shared regulatory axes (Canonical Components, CCs). CC scores
    are then aligned to genomic SNP positions to make binary annotations for
    stratified LD Score Regression (S-LDSC). The package provides an end-to-end
    pipeline from raw count data to S-LDSC-ready annotation files.
